article.headline: Fair Dickinson 69, Army 53
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- Chad Timberlake scored a game-high 18 points and had seven rebounds to lead Fairleigh Dickinson to a 69-53 win over Army Thursday night. Tamien Trent added 15 points for FDU (5-7). Colin Harris led Army (2-8) with 15 points. FDU never trailed, building a 34-22 halftime lead as Trent scored 14 of his points before the intermission. Army pulled within eight points twice in the second half, but FDU went on a 15-1 run, surging to its biggest lead of the night, 55-33, with 9:11 left. Gordon Klaiber scored eight points during the spurt.
